Program: Outlook
Title: Returning to Kashmir
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbs3z
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
The family returning to Kashmir after 15 years, despite continued fighting there. Also, what it's like to be a neurosurgeon. The nationality law in Israel preventing an Arab Israeli woman and her Palestinian husband from living together. Unemployment and poor job prospects for young people in Kenya. Educational pressures put on children by Japanese parents. Show less